However in Western countries and other places where prenatal gender determination is accepted and legal ( unlike in India) , the 4D imaging technology began to be used for 'Meet the Baby' Ultrasound scans where the parents as well as close relatives could watch the intrauterine fetus in spacious and comfortable family theater environment with high resolution monitors and large viewing screens. The premise for the scan in those places would be providing an opportunity for parental -fetal bonding , apart from the gender determination. Certain places offer a stand-alone 3D/4D ultrasound for these purposes only between 26 \u8211\'3f 34 weeks without offering a detailed 2D scan.}
