\par \pard\plain \s0\ql{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ltrpar\nowidctlpar\cf0\kerning1\hich\af7\langfe2052\dbch\af10\afs24\lang1081\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\loch\f3
As with most technology and practice, that permeates rapidly into India from the western world, the practice of 4D ultrasound has really caught on in India in this decade with every other ultrasound clinic / scan center offering the same with enticing fetal images. Though there are no stand alone centers offering the examinations, existing scan centers have pounced upon the 'opportunity' by offering the examinations as part of the routine 2D scans. It is being referred to as 'opportunity' in view of the charged fee being at least twice or thrice that of the routine 2D study. The most disconcerting aspect in this is the fact that it does not concur with the  Pre-conception and Pre-natal Diagnostic Techniques (PCPNDT) Act, at least in spirit. Though the 4D scan helps in depicting anomalies like  cleft lip, club feet and spinal anomalies to the parents better, most of the times, the examination is offered  as a source of entertainment and enjoyment of parents. }
